..."}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Returns the number of seconds in the given time intervals combined, rounded down to nearest integer.\n\nThis is a short variant of `int(timedelta(**kwargs).total_seconds())` with a\nfew extra named time intervals(year, month, quarter)\n\nA year is calculated as 365 days, a month is 30 days, a quarter is 1/4 of a year"]}, {"name": "pysj.main.months_in_interval", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "start", "type": {"name": "datetime", "xref": {"fqname": "datetime.datetime", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "end", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "datetime", "xref": {"fqname": "datetime.datetime", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["Yields months and year from the given interval (start -> end).\n\nstart: datetime\n    Start of interval\nend: datetime\n    Optional, end of interval. Todays date is used if end is not set.\n\nreturn: Iterable[Tuple[int, int]]"]}, {"name": "pysj.main.atomic_symlink", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "src", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "dst", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "raise_on_error", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Atomically creates a symlink *src* pointing to *dst*.\n\nAtomicity is achived trough renaming a temporary symlink with a random name.\n\nIf *raise_on_error* is True and the rename failes, the original exception is raised."]}, {"name": "pysj.main.flatten", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "iterable", "type": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Recursively flattens an iterable (depth first)\n\n# Usage\n\n```pycon\n>>> nested_list = [[(1.3, 3.0), \"string\", \"another string\"], [4, 5E2, sorted({\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"})]]\n>>> print(flatten(nested_list))\n[1.3, 3.0, \"string\", \"another string\", 4, 5E2, \"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]\n```\n"]}, {"name": "pysj.main.transpose", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "iterable", "type": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Transpose a list of lists with dimensions X=Y."]}, {"name": "pysj.main._extended_JSON_decoder_object_hook", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "d", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pysj.main.paginate", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "pagesize", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "data_attribute_name", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "max_num_requests", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "start_one", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "offset_is_n_of_elements", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Function returning a function yielding new urls if the data seems valid\n\nUsage\n-----\n\n    get_url = paginate(\"lol.lol?offset=OFFSET&pagesize=PAGESIZE\", max_num_requests=20, start_one=False)\n\n    data = None\n    while url := get_url(data):\n        data = requests.get(url)\n        # Do someting with the data, get_url will yield a new url a long as data is set to\n        # someting looking like a valid json response without an error attribute,\n        # and as long the data don't repeat."]}, {"name": "pysj.main.n_wise", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "n", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Yields *n* items from data like a gliding window, as long as there is enough elements in data to yield the full window.\nIf n == 3, and data = (1,2,3,4,5) the following items are yielded: (1,2,3), (2,3,4), (3,4,5).\n\nLike itertools.pairwise, but generalized to *n* items."]}, {"name": "pysj.main.triplewise", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pysj.main.moving_average", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "window_size", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pysj.main.take", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "n", "ty